long_desc.thetext:
When using the qx.data.Array.concat method, the bubbling event listeners on items are created with the wrong index names :

the section :

      Array.prototype.push.apply(this.__array, array);

      // add a listener to the new items
      for (var i = 0; i < array.length; i++) {
        this._registerEventChaining(array[i], null, this.__array.length + i);
      }


should be :

      var oldArrayLength = this.__array.length;
      Array.prototype.push.apply(this.__array, array);

      // add a listener to the new items
      for (var i = 0; i < array.length; i++) {
        this._registerEventChaining(array[i], null, oldArrayLength + i);
      }

because otherwise, index names are shifted and events are fired with index out of bounds
